Residents of Ngei ward in Mathare constituency yesterday said they will sue City Hall to stop the demolition of their structures over allegations they are inhabitable.Ngei MCA Dan Mutiso said many of the structures have been demolished. Residents say the houses are safe.In May, the National Construction Authority released a list of 204 unsafe residential buildings to be demolished.This came after a seven-storey flat collapsed in Huruma, killing 57 people.The buildings earmarked for demolition were in Dagoretti, Umoja, Thika Road, South B, Zimmerman, and Huruma.Huruma had the highest number of condemned buildings at 58, followed by Zimmerman with 28.In South B, 19 houses on Hazina Estate, owned by the National Social Security Fund managers, were earmarked for demolition but are yet to be pulled down.